docs.snippet: The Ames Test offered a fast and inexpensive way to identify carcinogens, leading to the banning of chemicals linked to cancer and birth defects.
docs.lead_paragraph: Bruce Nathan Ames, a biochemist who discovered a revolutionary method of detecting potential carcinogens, paving the way for the banning of many commonly used chemicals, died on Oct. 5 in Berkeley, Calif. He was 95.

headline.main: Bruce Ames, 95, Dies; Biochemist Discovered Test for Toxic Chemicals
headline.print_headline: Bruce Ames, 95, Who Found A Test for Toxic Chemicals, Dies

docs.abstract: NYT Article 8 - All-inclusive retreats around the world aim to cultivate wellness and longevity though high-tech tests, “biohacking” treatments, meditation, breath work and more.
docs.snippet: All-inclusive retreats around the world aim to cultivate wellness and longevity though high-tech tests, “biohacking” treatments, meditation, breath work and more.
docs.lead_paragraph: People used to strive simply to live as long as possible, but in recent years, that goal has taken on a new dimension: How long can you live in good health? “The focus now is on health span, not life span,” said Dr. Frank Lipman, a co-author of the 2020 book “The New Rules of Aging Well.” “We generally talk about extending someone’s life, but what’s the use if they’re suffering and disabled and can’t enjoy what they have?”

headline.main: 6 Vacations That Could Help You Live Longer and Healthier

docs.abstract: NYT Article 9 - A growing number of American adults have weakened immune systems, which can leave them vulnerable to severe illnesses.
docs.snippet: A growing number of American adults have weakened immune systems, which can leave them vulnerable to severe illnesses.
docs.lead_paragraph: Kaley Karaffa had just turned 28 when the reality of having a weakened immune system as a cancer patient started to sink in. A few weeks earlier, at an annual medical exam, Ms. Karaffa had expressed concern to her doctor about enlarged lymph nodes near her collarbone. Testing showed that Ms. Karaffa had a type of B-cell lymphoma, a cancer that affects the white blood cells, which are essential to fighting off infections.

headline.main: What Does It Mean to Be Immunocompromised?
headline.print_headline: Compromised Immunities Face Range of Attacks

docs.abstract: NYT Article 10 - The journalist Bob Woodward cited an unnamed aide saying that Donald J. Trump had spoken to Vladimir V. Putin as many as seven times since leaving office. Multiple sources say they cannot confirm that report.
docs.snippet: The journalist Bob Woodward cited an unnamed aide saying that Donald J. Trump had spoken to Vladimir V. Putin as many as seven times since leaving office. Multiple sources say they cannot confirm that report.
docs.lead_paragraph: Just weeks ahead of an election, Americans are once again being confronted with a familiar if vexing question that has never been definitively resolved: What is up with former President Donald J. Trump and President Vladimir V. Putin of Russia?

headline.main: Book Revives Questions About Trump’s Ties to Putin
headline.print_headline: Trump Secretly in Touch With Putin After Office, Book by Woodward Says
